{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17645797","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17645797"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:21:43+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:21:43+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18135"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18135","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18135"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10849"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78405"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10849","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10849"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18135"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63767"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25243"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25246"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26870"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78405","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78405"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe muscles of the posterior (extensor) compartment of the forearm are arranged in superficial and deep layers.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following muscles is located in the superficial layer?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Abductor pollicis longus","Extensor pollicis longus","Extensor carpi radialis brevis","Extensor pollicis brevis","Extensor indicis"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eextensor carpi radialis brevis\u003C/strong\u003E is one of the seven muscles in the superficial layer of the posterior forearm compartment. The other superficial muscles are extensor digitorum, extensor digiti minimi, extensor carpi ulnaris, anconeus, brachioradialis, and extensor carpi radialis longus.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options are all deep layer muscles:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExtensor pollicis longus\u003C/strong\u003E is in the deep layer\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAbductor pollicis longus\u003C/strong\u003E is in the deep layer\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExtensor pollicis brevis\u003C/strong\u003E is in the deep layer\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExtensor indicis\u003C/strong\u003E is in the deep layer\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe deep layer muscles are primarily responsible for thumb and index finger movements, while superficial muscles handle wrist extension and digit extension.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The superficial layer of the posterior forearm compartment contains seven muscles: extensor digitorum, extensor digiti minimi, extensor carpi ulnaris, anconeus, brachioradialis, extensor carpi radialis longus, and extensor carpi radialis brevis.","The deep layer of the posterior forearm compartment contains five muscles: abductor pollicis longus, extensor pollicis brevis, extensor pollicis longus, extensor indicis, and supinator."],"references":["West, S. G. (2019). Anatomy and physiology of the musculoskeletal system. Rheumatology Secrets E-Book: Rheumatology Secrets E-Book, 17","Miniato MA, Anand P, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder. 2023 Jul 24. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30725618","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press","McCausland C, Sawyer E, Eovaldi BJ, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder Muscles. 2023 Aug 8. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30521257","Paulsen, F., \u0026 Waschke, J. (Eds.). (2023). Sobotta Atlas of Anatomy, Vol. 1, English/Latin: General Anatomy and Musculoskeletal System (Vol. 1). Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63767"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18135"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63767","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/63767"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-10T16:24:35+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-12T09:08:36+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10849"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78405"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id